

	 
       I sit in your arms  Safe  sound  You tell me you love me  I look to the ground  I look up at him  And yearn to be free  Your arms were once comforting  Now they feel like chains  I want to feel his arms around me  But wait...  Everytime I leave your arms  I feel so insecure  So I always run back  To the safety in chains  And I break his heart  Everytime  I must get out  I must get away  Why does humanity always wish to be free from their chains  yet always run back to them once they are free?  
    
